headline: Freshpet faces slow sales on weaker spending, pet adoption trends
summary: Investing.com --Bank of America downgraded Freshpet to Neutral from Buy and cut its price objective to $60 from $81, saying demand for fresh pet food has weakened as consumers rein in spending and pet adoption rates slow.

headline: Q3 Earnings Approaching: Sector ETFs to Win/Lose
summary: Q3 earnings season kicks off with PEP and DAL -- sector ETFs like ITA, XLK, and XLF may gain, while CARZ, PKB and IYT could lag.

headline: Nestle Leaves Climate Alliance for Dairy Emission Reductions
summary: Nestle was a founding member of the international group started at the 2023 UN climate conference, alongside Kraft Heinz, Starbucks, Danone and General Mills.
